Members' liability
Each member of the charitable company undertakes to contribute to the assets of the company in the event of it
being wound up while he or she is a member, or within one year after he or she ceases to be a member, such
amount as may be required, not exceeding £10 for the debts and liabilities contracted before he or she ceases to
be a member.
No individual has a controlling interest in the charitable company.
